<TITLE> Russia may be forced to leave missile treaty:Putin </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 NOVO-OGARYOVO, Russia, Oct 12 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Russia will find it difficult to remain in a treaty on short and medium range missiles unless it is expanded to include other countries, Russian President Vladimir Putin said on Friday. "We need to bring things to a point so that this Russian-American agreement is given a global nature .... If we are not able to do this, it will be difficult for us to remain within the bounds of this agreement," Itar-Tass news agency quoted Putin as saying. It was not immediately clear which treaty Putin was referring to, but it appeared to be a 1987 treaty on the elimination of intermediate and short range missiles signed by Soviet leader Mikhail Gorbachev and U.S. President Ronald Reag
